1
00:00:42,542 --> 00:00:45,962
SOLD OUT ON YOU

2
00:00:47,714 --> 00:00:51,009
When I offered to bring you
Gojeuneok Bio's raw material,

3
00:00:51,092 --> 00:00:52,844
didn't you already know

4
00:00:52,927 --> 00:00:54,888
that it was just a temporary solution?

5
00:00:54,971 --> 00:00:56,055
So,

6
00:00:56,931 --> 00:00:58,683
what are you suggesting?

7
00:01:00,143 --> 00:01:02,771
Gojeuneok Bio just started developing
a new product.

8
00:01:03,938 --> 00:01:06,316
They're making cosmetics themselves?

9
00:01:06,399 --> 00:01:07,275
Yes.

10
00:01:12,864 --> 00:01:15,617
This isn't something to smile about.

11
00:01:18,953 --> 00:01:21,915
There was an incident five years ago

12
00:01:21,998 --> 00:01:23,917
that shook the whole country.

13
00:01:24,417 --> 00:01:26,044
The Good Morning Cream incident.

14
00:01:27,212 --> 00:01:29,130
And Lee Hae-seok

15
00:01:29,214 --> 00:01:31,508
is the one who made that cream.

16
00:01:33,134 --> 00:01:35,136
Once may have been a mistake,

17
00:01:35,220 --> 00:01:37,680
but if it keeps happening,

18
00:01:38,556 --> 00:01:39,933
that's intentional.

19
00:01:41,518 --> 00:01:42,769
This time,

20
00:01:44,729 --> 00:01:47,649
I'm going to make sure he can never
set foot in this industry again.

21
00:01:53,404 --> 00:01:54,739
I'm here.

22
00:01:56,407 --> 00:01:57,867
Mechoori.

23
00:02:01,704 --> 00:02:02,705
You're home.

24
00:02:02,789 --> 00:02:04,249
What is all this?

25
00:02:05,166 --> 00:02:07,085
Things I have to study.

26
00:02:07,168 --> 00:02:09,838
Regulations have changed a lot
in the past five years,

27
00:02:09,921 --> 00:02:12,632
and there are loads of new methods,
so I have a lot to catch up on.

28
00:02:13,174 --> 00:02:16,261
Aren't you tired
after working in the lab all day?

29
00:02:17,554 --> 00:02:18,680
Not at all.

30
00:02:20,098 --> 00:02:21,766
I have some stuff to read too.

31
00:03:05,935 --> 00:03:07,145
Focus.

32
00:03:15,403 --> 00:03:18,197
Stop distracting me with your beauty.

33
00:03:26,497 --> 00:03:28,791
Look at the time.

34
00:03:28,875 --> 00:03:30,084
Aren't you going to bed?

35
00:03:31,336 --> 00:03:32,337
After I finish this.

36
00:03:33,171 --> 00:03:35,340
Someone used to hate that phrase.

37
00:03:38,927 --> 00:03:40,345
Fine, I'll cut you some slack.

38
00:03:40,428 --> 00:03:42,388
You'd better go to bed after that one.

39
00:03:42,472 --> 00:03:44,057
Okay. Goodnight.

40
00:03:44,140 --> 00:03:45,558
Goodnight.

41
00:04:25,306 --> 00:04:27,600
Hey, you said you'd go to bed
after that file.

42
00:04:33,064 --> 00:04:34,274
Did you have trouble sleeping?

43
00:04:35,108 --> 00:04:36,484
I couldn't sleep at all.

44
00:04:43,533 --> 00:04:45,493
I decided to stop taking sleeping pills.

45
00:04:46,369 --> 00:04:47,912
You're not taking them anymore?

46
00:04:48,579 --> 00:04:49,914
Why? That's sudden.

47
00:04:50,415 --> 00:04:54,377
I just made the decision
after watching you earlier.

48
00:04:55,044 --> 00:04:56,504
I want to move forward like you too.

49
00:05:00,008 --> 00:05:02,802
I thought the past was holding me back,

50
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:05,763
but I just realized it was myself.

51
00:05:06,514 --> 00:05:09,350
I'm going to break free
from the cycle of insomnia

52
00:05:09,434 --> 00:05:10,768
and stop taking the pills.

53
00:05:13,438 --> 00:05:15,732
That's all good,
but just take them tonight.

54
00:05:16,607 --> 00:05:18,943
You should consult your doctor tomorrow.

55
00:05:19,861 --> 00:05:22,280
You need to taper off gradually…

56
00:05:22,363 --> 00:05:23,531
No.

57
00:05:23,614 --> 00:05:26,034
After all the sleep I lost,
I'm not taking them now.

58
00:05:30,079 --> 00:05:31,122
Let's go to bed now, then.

59
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,419
I just can't sleep.

60
00:05:40,506 --> 00:05:42,592
You don't have
to light the candle for me tonight.

61
00:05:42,675 --> 00:05:44,469
Go and sleep. You must be tired.

62
00:05:47,305 --> 00:05:49,223
I'm going to sleep here.

63
00:06:08,409 --> 00:06:09,410
Are your muscles relaxed?

64
00:06:10,453 --> 00:06:11,454
Yes.

65
00:06:15,958 --> 00:06:16,959
You got it, right?

66
00:06:18,669 --> 00:06:22,715
Loosen your muscles, starting from
your face down to your arms and legs.

67
00:06:22,799 --> 00:06:27,303
Just imagine that you're a jellyfish
floating in the ocean.

68
00:06:27,845 --> 00:06:31,849
Why would I be a jellyfish?
What on earth is this?

69
00:06:31,933 --> 00:06:35,186
It's a sleep method developed
by an American sports psychologist.

70
00:06:36,437 --> 00:06:40,483
According to the article, this will
allow you to fall asleep in two minutes.

71
00:06:40,566 --> 00:06:42,401
That sounds fake.

72
00:06:42,485 --> 00:06:44,278
- I'm wide awake.
- Focus.

73
00:06:46,322 --> 00:06:48,574
You are a jellyfish.

74
00:06:50,451 --> 00:06:51,744
Right. I'm a jellyfish.

75
00:06:51,828 --> 00:06:53,037
Close your eyes…

76
00:06:53,955 --> 00:06:56,707
and visualize what I say.

77
00:06:57,291 --> 00:07:00,962
You're lying in a canoe
floating on a calm lake

78
00:07:01,045 --> 00:07:03,589
on a warm spring day,

79
00:07:04,215 --> 00:07:07,135
looking up at the clear blue sky.

80
00:07:09,679 --> 00:07:11,055
That's right.

81
00:07:11,139 --> 00:07:12,598
I'm starting to feel drowsy.

82
00:07:12,682 --> 00:07:13,516
That's it.

83
00:07:14,767 --> 00:07:15,726
Good.

84
00:07:17,687 --> 00:07:20,982
That guy swimming over there is jacked.

85
00:07:22,108 --> 00:07:23,568
Are you here alone?

86
00:07:26,654 --> 00:07:27,738
Stop that!

87
00:07:28,739 --> 00:07:31,534
What? You told me to visualize it.

88
00:07:31,617 --> 00:07:33,286
Stop thinking.

89
00:07:33,369 --> 00:07:37,915
You have to consciously
tell yourself to stop thinking.

90
00:07:37,999 --> 00:07:39,333
That's what the article said.

91
00:07:39,417 --> 00:07:41,043
Geez, I was enjoying myself.

92
00:07:41,752 --> 00:07:44,046
- Then let me go back to the lake.
- The lake's all dry now.

93
00:07:44,130 --> 00:07:45,423
Just imagine

94
00:07:47,049 --> 00:07:48,968
that you're lying

95
00:07:49,802 --> 00:07:53,347
in a black hammock in complete darkness.

96
00:07:57,477 --> 00:08:00,271
Alone with you, Mechoori?

97
00:08:03,441 --> 00:08:04,567
Stop joking around.

98
00:08:04,650 --> 00:08:07,445
I'm just curious.

99
00:08:08,654 --> 00:08:12,366
How would we lie
side by side in a hammock?

100
00:08:13,034 --> 00:08:14,243
I'm warning you.

101
00:08:16,621 --> 00:08:19,540
Don't think. Just focus.

102
00:08:36,807 --> 00:08:38,100
You should sleep.

103
00:08:38,809 --> 00:08:40,978
You said you have to head out
early tomorrow.

104
00:09:01,832 --> 00:09:02,875
I won't think.

105
00:10:04,645 --> 00:10:06,939
HIT HOMESHOPPING

106
00:10:07,023 --> 00:10:10,318
The coffee addict
is refusing to drink coffee?

107
00:10:11,527 --> 00:10:13,446
Habits are addictive too.

108
00:10:13,529 --> 00:10:15,072
I made up my mind to change.

109
00:10:23,039 --> 00:10:24,123
Is it good?

110
00:10:25,124 --> 00:10:25,958
But…

111
00:10:26,834 --> 00:10:29,378
can we move into the shade? It's too hot.

112
00:10:30,921 --> 00:10:35,676
We have to get at least 15 minutes
of sunlight every day.

113
00:10:38,387 --> 00:10:39,847
Is this a PSA or what?

114
00:10:40,389 --> 00:10:42,141
That's very helpful.

115
00:10:42,224 --> 00:10:45,436
I should get in shape
before my own program starts.

116
00:10:48,606 --> 00:10:49,732
You mean Dam Ye-jin's Only1?

117
00:10:50,900 --> 00:10:52,735
We're in the weekend
prime time slot again?

118
00:10:52,818 --> 00:10:56,155
You'd better take good care
of your health. Understand?

119
00:11:01,744 --> 00:11:02,703
Sung-mi?

120
00:11:03,287 --> 00:11:04,830
You understand, right?

121
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:08,834
We did it!

122
00:11:08,918 --> 00:11:10,961
- That hurts.
- We made it!

123
00:11:13,589 --> 00:11:15,675
You have an item in mind, right?

124
00:11:15,758 --> 00:11:19,095
No, I have to start searching
for the perfect item.

125
00:11:19,178 --> 00:11:20,805
It's going to take ages.

126
00:11:20,888 --> 00:11:23,140
- Let's do this!
- Let's do this!

127
00:11:28,396 --> 00:11:31,482
WHITE FLOWER NOORI MUSHROOM EXTRACT

128
00:11:45,579 --> 00:11:47,915
So this is a new ingredient

129
00:11:47,998 --> 00:11:50,626
extracted from the white flower
noori mushroom with a new method?

130
00:11:51,210 --> 00:11:53,504
The wound's closing up much faster.

131
00:11:53,587 --> 00:11:55,464
Yes. See the incline here?

132
00:11:56,048 --> 00:11:57,842
I used this as the main ingredient,

133
00:11:57,925 --> 00:12:00,010
and it boosted the recovery speed
by 50 percent.

134
00:12:01,345 --> 00:12:03,305
I think I can create a cream

135
00:12:04,348 --> 00:12:05,683
that maximizes skin regeneration.

136
00:12:07,852 --> 00:12:08,853
Listen carefully.

137
00:12:09,437 --> 00:12:11,355
If you need anything,
just submit a request.

138
00:12:11,439 --> 00:12:13,274
Submit anything!
I'll get everything for you.

139
00:12:15,484 --> 00:12:18,446
You really are working hard.

140
00:12:18,529 --> 00:12:19,447
Hey!

141
00:12:19,530 --> 00:12:21,615
Remember the tofu and kimchi place
we always went to?

142
00:12:21,699 --> 00:12:22,992
They're still in business.

143
00:12:23,075 --> 00:12:25,744
Goodness, I didn't know that.

144
00:12:25,828 --> 00:12:27,163
Anyway, great timing.

145
00:12:27,246 --> 00:12:29,206
We were just about to celebrate.

146
00:12:29,290 --> 00:12:30,541
Why? Is there good news?

147
00:12:32,376 --> 00:12:35,880
Gojeuneok Bio's first cosmetic product
has just been decided.

148
00:12:35,963 --> 00:12:37,631
It'll be a regenerative cream.

149
00:12:39,175 --> 00:12:41,427
Mr. Lee here developed a new material

150
00:12:41,510 --> 00:12:43,721
with the white flower noori mushroom…

151
00:12:44,638 --> 00:12:45,473
and he slayed.

152
00:12:47,766 --> 00:12:50,227
What do I do? I love you so much.

153
00:12:50,311 --> 00:12:51,854
You want me to cut it out?

154
00:12:51,937 --> 00:12:54,231
Anyway, LFI.

155
00:12:55,149 --> 00:12:56,442
Look forward to it.

156
00:12:57,526 --> 00:12:58,569
Right.

157
00:12:58,652 --> 00:13:00,613
Anyway, congrats.

158
00:13:01,405 --> 00:13:03,657
But you should be cautious.

159
00:13:03,741 --> 00:13:06,952
Your raw material is already expensive,

160
00:13:07,036 --> 00:13:10,498
so with processing added,
the unit price will be pretty high.

161
00:13:10,581 --> 00:13:12,917
Then you won't have an advantage
in the market.

162
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:15,169
Did you forget? I'm Kang Mu-won.

163
00:13:15,252 --> 00:13:17,129
If I was after money,
I wouldn't have started.

164
00:13:17,213 --> 00:13:20,633
Mu-won, you're being so naive.

165
00:13:21,425 --> 00:13:25,012
A businessman
should always prioritize margins.

166
00:13:28,307 --> 00:13:30,017
Gosh, I have a bad habit of meddling.

167
00:13:30,100 --> 00:13:31,352
I'm sure you'll do fine.

168
00:13:31,435 --> 00:13:33,521
Let's eat! Come on, sit.

169
00:14:01,757 --> 00:14:03,717
Mechoori.

170
00:14:04,593 --> 00:14:05,594
You're here.

171
00:14:05,678 --> 00:14:07,221
What's the occasion?

172
00:14:07,304 --> 00:14:08,639
You're all dressed up.

173
00:14:09,306 --> 00:14:10,975
And you invited me to a fancy restaurant.

174
00:14:11,559 --> 00:14:12,560
Sit down.

175
00:14:13,143 --> 00:14:14,687
No way…

176
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:17,982
It can't be, right?

177
00:14:20,526 --> 00:14:22,027
I'm making a proposal.

178
00:14:22,111 --> 00:14:23,737
- To you.
- Wait.

179
00:14:25,239 --> 00:14:27,825
Hey, you should've given me a hint.

180
00:14:27,908 --> 00:14:30,995
Then I would've dressed up a bit too.

181
00:14:31,078 --> 00:14:32,538
I thought there was no way…

182
00:14:32,621 --> 00:14:34,123
You mean it?

183
00:14:48,304 --> 00:14:50,764
I'm making a product listing proposal,

184
00:14:50,848 --> 00:14:52,266
Ms. Dam Ye-jin.

185
00:14:54,643 --> 00:14:55,644
Product listing?

186
00:15:01,108 --> 00:15:02,109
GOJEUNEOK BIO CREAM

187
00:15:02,192 --> 00:15:04,111
DAM YE-JIN'S ONLY1,
PRODUCT PLACEMENT PROPOSAL

188
00:15:06,363 --> 00:15:07,740
Without you,

189
00:15:07,823 --> 00:15:10,367
I wouldn't even have started
developing this cream.

190
00:15:12,953 --> 00:15:14,747
Will you join me in finishing

191
00:15:15,581 --> 00:15:16,832
this project?

192
00:15:20,586 --> 00:15:23,047
Keep doubting me, and keep me on my toes.

193
00:15:24,465 --> 00:15:25,966
If I'm working with you,

194
00:15:27,051 --> 00:15:29,219
I won't feel worried.

195
00:15:52,993 --> 00:15:54,370
GOJEUNEOK BIO

196
00:16:42,918 --> 00:16:43,961
What are you looking for?

197
00:16:44,670 --> 00:16:45,713
I need to check something.

198
00:16:47,297 --> 00:16:49,883
You're not checking all of this, are you?

199
00:16:49,967 --> 00:16:52,511
I have no choice.
I have to look through everything.

200
00:16:53,637 --> 00:16:55,097
Mechoori.

201
00:16:55,180 --> 00:16:57,558
Let me give you a tip.

202
00:17:02,479 --> 00:17:03,522
Here.

203
00:17:03,605 --> 00:17:04,898
Explain what you're looking for.

204
00:17:08,736 --> 00:17:11,321
I'm looking for data
on the antimicrobial effects

205
00:17:11,405 --> 00:17:12,906
of major medicinal mushroom extracts

206
00:17:12,990 --> 00:17:14,867
studied by Seohan University's
research team.

207
00:17:15,868 --> 00:17:16,910
The paper you mentioned

208
00:17:16,994 --> 00:17:20,164
is part of the research on ingredients
that are effective and safe

209
00:17:20,247 --> 00:17:22,041
for sensitive skin.

210
00:17:22,124 --> 00:17:23,625
The antimicrobial test results

211
00:17:23,709 --> 00:17:26,628
against five microorganisms
that cause skin diseases

212
00:17:26,712 --> 00:17:30,966
showed an MIC of 19.72 µg/mL.

213
00:17:31,967 --> 00:17:36,013
Honestly, I was pleased
with the seventh sample too.

214
00:17:36,096 --> 00:17:37,639
I think we're finally getting there.

215
00:17:37,723 --> 00:17:39,516
- We can't be sure yet.
- We can't be sure yet.

216
00:17:44,521 --> 00:17:45,606
All right.

217
00:17:45,689 --> 00:17:47,900
Let's keep up this energy and continue.

218
00:17:47,983 --> 00:17:49,818
- Let's do this.
- Let's do this.

219
00:17:49,902 --> 00:17:52,946
You know, everything's fine, but…

220
00:17:55,074 --> 00:17:56,533
That's the scariest phrase.

221
00:17:58,911 --> 00:18:02,539
The smell of this white flower
noori mushroom bothers me a bit.

222
00:18:02,623 --> 00:18:05,918
A distinct fragrance
leads to mixed reactions,

223
00:18:06,001 --> 00:18:07,544
and that affects sales directly.

224
00:18:07,628 --> 00:18:10,631
Are you suggesting we add
synthetic fragrance just for sales?

225
00:18:10,714 --> 00:18:13,217
I'm talking about market viability.

226
00:18:13,300 --> 00:18:15,552
We want as many people as possible

227
00:18:15,636 --> 00:18:17,971
to use Gojeuneok's cream
and benefit from it, right?

228
00:18:18,055 --> 00:18:21,350
The scent is a matter of preference.
There isn't a right answer.

229
00:18:21,433 --> 00:18:22,810
Still…

230
00:18:22,893 --> 00:18:27,606
How many people would actually
say they like this smell?

231
00:18:31,401 --> 00:18:34,488
I believe we can effectively portray
Gojeuneok's natural concept--

232
00:18:34,571 --> 00:18:37,282
If that's your purpose,
it will be better to use

233
00:18:37,366 --> 00:18:39,868
citrus, marine, or woody scents
that are widely popular.

234
00:18:40,828 --> 00:18:42,621
Why don't we discuss what's better--

235
00:18:42,704 --> 00:18:43,997
Ms. Dam Ye-jin!

236
00:18:48,919 --> 00:18:52,923
I'm the developer of this cream,
and I know what's best for it.

237
00:18:53,799 --> 00:18:55,551
Mr. Lee Hae-seok.

238
00:18:56,468 --> 00:18:59,346
I'm just suggesting making another reason
for the customers to buy this.

239
00:18:59,429 --> 00:19:02,474
Why would luxury brands add
synthetic fragrances to their products?

240
00:19:02,558 --> 00:19:05,644
The scent itself
provides comfort and satisfaction.

241
00:19:05,727 --> 00:19:07,604
Once they experience this cream's effects,

242
00:19:07,688 --> 00:19:11,191
they'll end up liking this scent
that you hate so much.

243
00:19:13,485 --> 00:19:17,656
Mr. Lee, isn't this a meeting
to exchange feedback?

244
00:19:17,739 --> 00:19:20,033
It seems like you're not open
to any feedback at all.

245
00:19:20,117 --> 00:19:23,203
Ms. Dam, I would like to accept feedback
if it helps our product.

246
00:19:23,287 --> 00:19:24,454
Is this not helpful?

247
00:19:24,538 --> 00:19:25,539
I'm not sure.

248
00:19:28,709 --> 00:19:29,626
Let's take a break.

249
00:19:29,710 --> 00:19:31,420
Let's resume in 15 minutes.

250
00:19:45,475 --> 00:19:47,603
Will we really be able to sell this cream?

251
00:19:48,520 --> 00:19:50,480
Something's bound to happen
between those two.

252
00:19:50,564 --> 00:19:52,399
Then what about our broadcast?

253
00:19:55,360 --> 00:19:57,404
Geez.

254
00:20:04,328 --> 00:20:05,329
He's alone.

255
00:20:05,412 --> 00:20:07,164
They must have gotten into a fight!

256
00:20:07,748 --> 00:20:08,874
Where's Dam Ye-jin?

257
00:20:12,377 --> 00:20:14,463
I think she's with him.

258
00:20:14,546 --> 00:20:15,380
What?

259
00:20:23,013 --> 00:20:25,432
Hey, can't you…

260
00:20:26,058 --> 00:20:28,101
speak a bit more gently?

261
00:20:30,395 --> 00:20:31,521
I'll be more careful.

262
00:20:31,605 --> 00:20:33,190
That is a warning.

263
00:20:34,983 --> 00:20:36,902
We were worried for nothing.

264
00:20:37,778 --> 00:20:38,946
Let's go.

265
00:20:40,322 --> 00:20:42,199
- Honey potato!
- Cherry tomato!

266
00:20:42,282 --> 00:20:44,451
Cherry tomato's on a break.

267
00:20:44,534 --> 00:20:45,869
- Really?
- Did you have lunch?

268
00:20:45,953 --> 00:20:46,995
Of course.

269
00:20:47,079 --> 00:20:49,373
- What did you have?
- I had noodles.

270
00:20:56,380 --> 00:20:58,090
The texture is the same…

271
00:20:59,716 --> 00:21:01,677
And that funky smell too.

272
00:21:03,262 --> 00:21:04,263
Mr. Lee.

273
00:21:04,930 --> 00:21:07,599
The pilot test matches the sample.

274
00:21:09,518 --> 00:21:12,312
ASSESSMENT
PASS

275
00:21:17,192 --> 00:21:19,027
Great job.

276
00:21:20,028 --> 00:21:21,697
Good job.

277
00:21:22,406 --> 00:21:24,032
Great job.

278
00:21:24,116 --> 00:21:25,617
Have you decided on the name?

279
00:21:26,118 --> 00:21:29,121
We should finalize the name
before we go into production.

280
00:21:29,663 --> 00:21:31,665
I'm going to ask a naming specialist.

281
00:21:33,208 --> 00:21:34,418
Did you really clean it?

282
00:21:34,501 --> 00:21:36,628
- I did.
- Are you sure?

283
00:21:36,712 --> 00:21:38,255
I'm telling you, I did.

284
00:21:38,338 --> 00:21:39,840
No way. It's the same as yesterday.

285
00:21:39,923 --> 00:21:40,882
I did.

286
00:21:40,966 --> 00:21:42,592
- Just go.
- Som-yi.

287
00:21:42,676 --> 00:21:44,219
Mechoori.

288
00:21:44,303 --> 00:21:46,221
You're back from school?

289
00:21:48,640 --> 00:21:50,851
Som-yi, look.

290
00:21:53,979 --> 00:21:54,980
What is it?

291
00:21:56,356 --> 00:21:58,066
I made this cream.

292
00:21:58,150 --> 00:21:59,901
Wow, really?

293
00:21:59,985 --> 00:22:01,528
What's it made of?

294
00:22:02,529 --> 00:22:04,865
You know the white flower
noori mushroom, right?

295
00:22:04,948 --> 00:22:06,616
That and some other stuff.

296
00:22:07,409 --> 00:22:08,410
Som-yi.

297
00:22:09,202 --> 00:22:11,621
What should I name it?

298
00:22:12,122 --> 00:22:14,041
I'd like you to decide.

299
00:22:14,124 --> 00:22:15,417
The name?

300
00:22:18,128 --> 00:22:19,087
Noori Cream.

301
00:22:20,005 --> 00:22:20,839
Noori Cream?

302
00:22:21,840 --> 00:22:24,301
Hey, that's so tacky.

303
00:22:25,302 --> 00:22:29,348
I learned in school that "noori"
means "the whole world."

304
00:22:29,431 --> 00:22:30,515
It could mean

305
00:22:30,599 --> 00:22:33,060
that the whole world
will end up using this cream.

306
00:22:33,143 --> 00:22:34,728
Isn't that awesome?

307
00:22:37,898 --> 00:22:38,982
Noori Cream.

308
00:22:40,067 --> 00:22:41,068
I like it.

309
00:22:41,860 --> 00:22:43,028
See?

310
00:22:43,111 --> 00:22:44,738
Mechoori, can I use this?

311
00:22:50,160 --> 00:22:52,037
Of course. We can use it together.

312
00:22:52,120 --> 00:22:53,121
No.

313
00:22:53,205 --> 00:22:54,081
It's mine.

314
00:22:54,164 --> 00:22:56,958
I'll try this after I wash my face.

315
00:23:01,129 --> 00:23:02,839
Noori Cream is going to be a huge hit.

316
00:23:02,923 --> 00:23:04,424
It made that lazyhead wash her face.

317
00:23:07,385 --> 00:23:08,804
Right, Jin-yi…

318
00:23:11,431 --> 00:23:12,599
I was asked to give you this.

319
00:23:13,600 --> 00:23:14,601
By who?

320
00:23:19,940 --> 00:23:23,568
HIT's open recruitment deadline
is midnight today.

321
00:23:23,652 --> 00:23:26,905
I really hope you seize this chance
to show your talent.

322
00:23:29,741 --> 00:23:31,409
How long are you going to stay like that?

323
00:23:32,035 --> 00:23:34,287
I've been so excited for this moment.

324
00:23:34,371 --> 00:23:35,914
I want it to be a surprise.

325
00:23:38,250 --> 00:23:39,167
What was that?

326
00:23:39,793 --> 00:23:40,669
Hang on.

327
00:23:42,629 --> 00:23:43,463
All right.

328
00:23:48,176 --> 00:23:49,886
Are we here now? Can I open my eyes?

329
00:23:49,970 --> 00:23:51,429
Just a bit more.

330
00:23:52,722 --> 00:23:53,932
Now?

331
00:23:54,683 --> 00:23:56,143
Turn around here.

332
00:23:56,226 --> 00:23:58,019
Give me a countdown. Come on.

333
00:23:58,979 --> 00:23:59,980
Three, two--

334
00:24:04,901 --> 00:24:05,902
It's you.

335
00:24:07,112 --> 00:24:08,780
I was desperate to see you.

336
00:24:08,864 --> 00:24:11,241
Wow, you look so cool.

337
00:24:11,324 --> 00:24:12,367
Are you that happy?

338
00:24:12,450 --> 00:24:14,119
Isn't it obvious?

339
00:24:15,620 --> 00:24:16,496
Are you crying?

340
00:24:17,831 --> 00:24:19,166
Why would you cry over this?

341
00:24:19,249 --> 00:24:20,333
How could I not?

342
00:24:20,417 --> 00:24:22,085
You worked so hard to make this.

343
00:24:22,169 --> 00:24:24,045
Of course, I'd cry.

344
00:24:28,508 --> 00:24:29,885
You did an amazing job.

345
00:24:30,594 --> 00:24:32,012
I knew you could do it.

346
00:24:32,095 --> 00:24:33,430
Thank you

347
00:24:33,513 --> 00:24:34,890
for encouraging me every day.

348
00:24:36,141 --> 00:24:37,601
That kept me going.

349
00:24:48,820 --> 00:24:49,988
Come in.

350
00:24:51,281 --> 00:24:52,157
Director.

351
00:24:53,325 --> 00:24:54,201
Hey.

352
00:24:57,162 --> 00:24:58,330
You've waited a long time.

353
00:24:58,413 --> 00:25:01,249
I brought my first item
for Dam Ye-jin's Only1.

354
00:25:03,585 --> 00:25:05,128
GOJEUNEOK BIO REGENERATIVE CREAM

355
00:25:05,212 --> 00:25:06,087
Gojeuneok Bio…

356
00:25:07,631 --> 00:25:09,716
The raw material company
for La Fin Essence?

357
00:25:09,799 --> 00:25:13,011
Yes. And that meticulous company
made their first cosmetic product.

358
00:25:14,387 --> 00:25:15,805
Are you confident about this?

359
00:25:15,889 --> 00:25:16,723
Absolutely.

360
00:25:23,063 --> 00:25:23,980
Great job.

361
00:25:26,399 --> 00:25:27,609
Thanks.

362
00:25:30,111 --> 00:25:31,071
All right.

363
00:25:32,364 --> 00:25:35,200
You've all put in so much work
for our Noori Cream.

364
00:25:39,829 --> 00:25:41,915
Do you know what my credit card

365
00:25:41,998 --> 00:25:44,251
and you have in common?

366
00:25:44,334 --> 00:25:45,710
- No.
- What is it?

367
00:25:45,794 --> 00:25:47,337
There is no limit.

368
00:25:48,463 --> 00:25:49,631
That's awesome!

369
00:25:50,840 --> 00:25:53,343
Eat as much as you want,
and make sure to get drunk.

370
00:25:53,426 --> 00:25:54,427
For Noori Cream!

371
00:25:54,970 --> 00:25:56,638
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

372
00:26:03,436 --> 00:26:05,188
What are you doing? That's alcohol.

373
00:26:05,272 --> 00:26:07,274
I can drink now,

374
00:26:07,357 --> 00:26:08,775
thanks to someone.

375
00:26:12,529 --> 00:26:13,989
Let's just eat.

376
00:26:14,072 --> 00:26:16,366
Mechoori, this is really tasty.

377
00:26:16,449 --> 00:26:17,492
Try it.

378
00:26:17,575 --> 00:26:18,702
You should eat.

379
00:26:19,911 --> 00:26:22,330
- Go on, try it first.
- Only if you eat first.

380
00:26:23,039 --> 00:26:25,667
Gosh. Well, then…

381
00:26:25,750 --> 00:26:27,502
- Excuse me.
- My gosh.

382
00:26:28,336 --> 00:26:29,337
Here, eat this first.

383
00:26:29,421 --> 00:26:31,589
I picked the wrong seat.

384
00:26:35,552 --> 00:26:36,553
Isn't it good?

385
00:26:38,596 --> 00:26:40,140
Potatoes.

386
00:26:42,267 --> 00:26:44,102
I miss my potato.

387
00:26:56,406 --> 00:26:59,451
Can I have another bottle of beer?

388
00:27:00,160 --> 00:27:01,578
That's enough.

389
00:27:01,661 --> 00:27:03,747
Go home.

390
00:27:05,957 --> 00:27:07,959
Hey, cherry tomato.

391
00:27:08,043 --> 00:27:09,627
Honey potato.

392
00:27:09,711 --> 00:27:10,879
What are you doing here?

393
00:27:12,088 --> 00:27:13,089
You said you miss me.

394
00:27:14,674 --> 00:27:17,594
You came all the way here
just because I said that?

395
00:27:19,012 --> 00:27:21,890
If I tell you to die,
would you really die for me?

396
00:27:28,396 --> 00:27:29,356
You're so cute.

397
00:27:30,065 --> 00:27:31,274
Park Kwang-mo, you're so cute.

398
00:27:32,317 --> 00:27:33,318
So cute.

399
00:27:33,401 --> 00:27:36,363
You're so, so, so adorable.

400
00:27:36,446 --> 00:27:37,739
Adorable?

401
00:27:39,366 --> 00:27:42,869
I'm not just adorable, you know.

402
00:27:50,210 --> 00:27:51,586
You… You got that?

403
00:28:20,865 --> 00:28:27,580
- So cute!
- So cute!

404
00:28:45,640 --> 00:28:46,474
Mr. Seo.

405
00:28:56,067 --> 00:29:00,363
It always seems to rain when I meet you.

406
00:29:01,406 --> 00:29:02,907
Right?

407
00:29:03,533 --> 00:29:07,036
But the weather is usually nice
when I go somewhere.

408
00:29:07,662 --> 00:29:10,915
I think you're the one
who's summoning the rain.

409
00:29:16,755 --> 00:29:19,799
Why didn't you come that day?

410
00:29:23,803 --> 00:29:25,054
Well…

411
00:29:25,138 --> 00:29:26,973
Since it's raining,

412
00:29:28,224 --> 00:29:30,310
this seems like
an appropriate moment to ask.

413
00:29:35,523 --> 00:29:37,859
If you believe in fate,

414
00:29:37,942 --> 00:29:41,488
why don't we just meet here tomorrow?

415
00:29:41,571 --> 00:29:43,114
I wanted to believe in fate.

416
00:29:43,907 --> 00:29:44,908
It had been

417
00:29:46,117 --> 00:29:48,077
a long time since anyone

418
00:29:49,120 --> 00:29:50,914
looked at me with such sparkling eyes.

419
00:29:51,664 --> 00:29:53,583
I should be there by 12:00 p.m.,

420
00:29:54,793 --> 00:29:56,461
so I should wake up at 10:00 a.m.

421
00:29:57,128 --> 00:29:59,214
No, I'll get up at 9:30 a.m.

422
00:30:08,932 --> 00:30:13,561
I wanted to get a good night's sleep
and show up looking refreshed…

423
00:30:21,694 --> 00:30:23,905
But when I woke up, it was evening.

424
00:30:25,490 --> 00:30:29,744
The new meds I was prescribed
didn't agree with me.

425
00:30:49,430 --> 00:30:50,431
I see.

426
00:30:54,143 --> 00:30:56,062
Though it's all in the past,

427
00:30:56,938 --> 00:31:00,024
I don't want to dismiss
the time I spent with you.

428
00:31:01,192 --> 00:31:02,819
I really had a great time.

429
00:31:03,862 --> 00:31:08,491
And those memories helped me
whenever things were tough.

430
00:31:10,869 --> 00:31:11,870
Thank you

431
00:31:12,537 --> 00:31:14,080
for cherishing those memories.

432
00:31:15,707 --> 00:31:17,667
The time I spent with you

433
00:31:18,418 --> 00:31:20,587
will be a valuable memory for me too.

434
00:31:21,880 --> 00:31:26,050
Thanks to your sincerity
and dedication to your work,

435
00:31:27,552 --> 00:31:29,721
I figured out
what sort of path I want to take.

436
00:31:30,471 --> 00:31:31,472
Maybe that's why…

437
00:31:32,932 --> 00:31:35,143
the Eric Seo I saw while working

438
00:31:35,226 --> 00:31:38,396
was much cooler than the man
three years ago under that umbrella.

439
00:31:39,480 --> 00:31:40,481
Really?

440
00:31:45,111 --> 00:31:48,072
Do you know the word "blindly"?

441
00:31:50,116 --> 00:31:53,661
It means doing something
without any plans or thoughts.

442
00:31:55,747 --> 00:31:56,748
That sounds nice.

443
00:31:56,831 --> 00:32:00,126
But that's actually pretty difficult.

444
00:32:00,209 --> 00:32:03,463
So, how about walking blindly with me?

445
00:32:03,546 --> 00:32:05,423
I'll give you a relaxing tour.

446
00:32:05,506 --> 00:32:06,799
Let's go, stranger.

447
00:32:27,612 --> 00:32:28,696
DAM YE-JIN'S ONLY1

448
00:32:31,491 --> 00:32:35,161
We're doing a lucky draw event
where you can win various rewards

449
00:32:35,244 --> 00:32:38,748
from the Noori Cream to a discount code
you can use for the launch broadcast.

450
00:32:38,831 --> 00:32:40,750
This is why you're our ace host.

451
00:32:41,626 --> 00:32:45,713
The Noori Cream is the hottest item
among the merchandisers right now.

452
00:32:45,797 --> 00:32:49,550
Everyone was wondering how you found
such a precious gem

453
00:32:49,634 --> 00:32:51,636
- and was praising you--
- Mr. Hwang.

454
00:32:52,720 --> 00:32:54,889
You should give more precise details.

455
00:32:54,973 --> 00:32:56,641
How exactly did they praise me?

456
00:32:56,724 --> 00:32:59,894
Right. The Noori Cream
pre-release trial event.

457
00:33:00,478 --> 00:33:01,521
Did you know

458
00:33:01,604 --> 00:33:04,774
we were selecting 30 people,
but there were over 500 applicants?

459
00:33:04,857 --> 00:33:08,111
It was so tough doing the draw.

460
00:33:08,194 --> 00:33:09,612
When can we see the reviews?

461
00:33:09,696 --> 00:33:10,530
In two weeks.

462
00:33:10,613 --> 00:33:13,241
I'll organize all the reviews
when they're out

463
00:33:13,324 --> 00:33:14,784
and share them with you.

464
00:33:14,867 --> 00:33:17,495
We have to use the reviews
for our inserts,

465
00:33:17,578 --> 00:33:19,163
so make sure to get all the photos.

466
00:33:25,503 --> 00:33:28,506
I brought salt bread made
with Guérande sea salt from France…

467
00:33:28,589 --> 00:33:30,925
And you're already drinking coffee.

468
00:33:31,801 --> 00:33:33,344
Mr. Cha,

469
00:33:34,929 --> 00:33:36,764
you're really photogenic.

470
00:33:38,099 --> 00:33:38,933
What?

471
00:33:39,600 --> 00:33:40,435
Bring them over.

472
00:33:50,778 --> 00:33:52,822
He passed the secretary interview
with these photos.

473
00:33:52,905 --> 00:33:53,823
Impressive, right?

474
00:33:59,120 --> 00:34:00,580
Eat that yourself.

475
00:34:01,122 --> 00:34:02,290
You'll need it.

476
00:34:15,053 --> 00:34:16,054
Did you play basketball?

477
00:34:19,640 --> 00:34:20,475
I'm moving in.

478
00:34:22,769 --> 00:34:24,103
Block properly.

479
00:34:29,859 --> 00:34:30,902
What?

480
00:34:30,985 --> 00:34:32,236
- That young man…
- Isn't he cold?

481
00:34:35,531 --> 00:34:37,158
- I'm not cold…
- Mr. Cha!

482
00:34:37,241 --> 00:34:38,701
What happened?

483
00:34:38,785 --> 00:34:39,619
I'm sorry.

484
00:34:39,702 --> 00:34:40,953
I got caught.

485
00:34:41,037 --> 00:34:42,288
What…

486
00:34:42,371 --> 00:34:43,498
Did you get hit?

487
00:34:43,998 --> 00:34:45,416
I'm fine.

488
00:34:45,500 --> 00:34:47,001
No, you're not.

489
00:34:47,085 --> 00:34:51,631
Still, I managed to pull one over on them.

490
00:35:05,186 --> 00:35:06,020
Right.

491
00:35:06,104 --> 00:35:10,149
I'll find something in there, even if
I have to look through it all night.

492
00:35:11,901 --> 00:35:15,571
By the way, it'll be hard
tracking Ms. Michelle's movements now.

493
00:35:15,655 --> 00:35:16,823
What do we do?

494
00:35:20,118 --> 00:35:22,703
GOJEUNEOK BIO

495
00:35:26,124 --> 00:35:27,125
Mr. Lee.

496
00:35:27,208 --> 00:35:28,459
Yes?

497
00:35:29,502 --> 00:35:30,920
There's something you should see.

498
00:35:44,475 --> 00:35:46,102
The person claiming to be the victim

499
00:35:46,185 --> 00:35:48,062
is a beauty creator called Sensitive Assi.

500
00:35:48,646 --> 00:35:50,648
She has an inflammatory skin condition.

501
00:35:51,274 --> 00:35:53,901
Since she's a well-known creator
and the content's pretty intense,

502
00:35:53,985 --> 00:35:56,487
it's spreading quickly
on social media and online communities.

503
00:35:56,571 --> 00:35:58,281
It's just her claim.

504
00:35:59,031 --> 00:36:00,992
She could've eaten something
that caused it.

505
00:36:01,075 --> 00:36:03,703
We ran this through numerous testing labs.

506
00:36:03,786 --> 00:36:05,788
It can't be true.

507
00:36:07,540 --> 00:36:09,167
Let me make a call.

508
00:36:11,085 --> 00:36:12,253
MECHOORI

509
00:36:13,546 --> 00:36:14,547
Hello?

510
00:36:14,630 --> 00:36:17,049
Ms. Dam, you saw the post, right?

511
00:36:17,133 --> 00:36:18,801
We're looking into this matter right now.

512
00:36:18,885 --> 00:36:20,303
CEO LEE HAE-SEOK

513
00:36:25,683 --> 00:36:27,685
I'll call you again later.

514
00:36:28,311 --> 00:36:29,896
Is something going on?

515
00:36:30,688 --> 00:36:31,939
Mechoori.

516
00:36:33,816 --> 00:36:36,652
ANOTHER GOOD MORNING CREAM INCIDENT?
RESEARCHER RETURNS WITHOUT REMORSE

517
00:36:51,375 --> 00:36:52,376
DEOKPUNG HID LEE HAE-SEOK

518
00:36:52,460 --> 00:36:56,505
Mechoori, a bunch of people
stormed in last night

519
00:36:56,589 --> 00:36:59,133
and made a total mess in the village.

520
00:36:59,217 --> 00:37:00,384
What should we do?

521
00:37:00,468 --> 00:37:02,011
I thought you should know, at least.

522
00:37:02,094 --> 00:37:03,304
Goodness.

523
00:37:03,387 --> 00:37:05,181
TAKE RESPONSIBILITY
CRIMINAL LEE HAE-SEOK OUT

524
00:37:05,264 --> 00:37:06,599
What do I do?

525
00:37:13,189 --> 00:37:14,232
This is ridiculous.

526
00:37:14,315 --> 00:37:15,441
Over there.

527
00:37:15,524 --> 00:37:16,984
Where? Let's hurry.

528
00:37:17,652 --> 00:37:18,611
This is nonsense.

529
00:37:21,364 --> 00:37:23,074
WHAT YOU MADE IS POISON, NOT CREAM

530
00:37:23,157 --> 00:37:24,325
"Poison, not cream"?

531
00:37:25,243 --> 00:37:26,452
Jin-yi, who are they?

532
00:37:26,535 --> 00:37:27,745
Let's go inside.

533
00:37:27,828 --> 00:37:29,747
Why? They're heading to Mechoori's house.

534
00:37:29,830 --> 00:37:32,208
Let's just go inside, all right?

535
00:37:39,966 --> 00:37:41,092
You'll hurt someone!

536
00:37:41,175 --> 00:37:43,302
Please, calm down and talk this out.

537
00:37:43,386 --> 00:37:44,595
Tell him to get out here!

538
00:37:44,679 --> 00:37:46,264
You all know him, don't you?

539
00:37:46,973 --> 00:37:49,016
Just talk it out. Please.

540
00:37:49,100 --> 00:37:49,934
He's here.

541
00:37:50,726 --> 00:37:51,560
That jerk's here.

542
00:37:55,189 --> 00:37:57,024
You're finally showing your face.

543
00:37:57,108 --> 00:37:59,485
You were hiding here all along
after ruining my kid's skin?

544
00:37:59,568 --> 00:38:02,071
Look at my face.

545
00:38:02,154 --> 00:38:03,864
You see what you did to me?

546
00:38:03,948 --> 00:38:05,908
Fix what you did!

547
00:38:05,992 --> 00:38:09,829
Fix my kid's face
and all our lives you ruined!

548
00:38:09,912 --> 00:38:11,956
This isn't going to solve anything!

549
00:38:12,039 --> 00:38:13,916
Talk this out! People will get hurt!

550
00:38:14,000 --> 00:38:14,959
Are you okay, Mechoori?

551
00:38:15,042 --> 00:38:18,713
Everyone, please calm down.
Let's talk this over, all right?

552
00:38:18,796 --> 00:38:20,881
My child can't even wear
short sleeves in summer

553
00:38:20,965 --> 00:38:22,174
or go to a swimming pool

554
00:38:22,258 --> 00:38:24,593
because of the cream he made!

555
00:38:25,886 --> 00:38:26,887
I'm sorry.

556
00:38:27,680 --> 00:38:28,556
Hey!

557
00:38:28,639 --> 00:38:31,600
"Sorry"? You try using
that cream, you jerk!

558
00:38:33,853 --> 00:38:34,854
Please, calm down!

559
00:38:34,937 --> 00:38:36,605
Move aside!

560
00:38:38,399 --> 00:38:39,692
Jong-il!

561
00:38:39,775 --> 00:38:40,943
Jong-il.

562
00:38:41,027 --> 00:38:42,570
- Are you hurt?
- Are you okay?

563
00:38:42,653 --> 00:38:44,697
You must've hurt your back. What do we do?

564
00:38:44,780 --> 00:38:46,782
Why did you have to butt in like that?

565
00:38:46,866 --> 00:38:48,367
Are you kidding me?

566
00:38:48,451 --> 00:38:49,744
Look here!

567
00:38:49,827 --> 00:38:52,496
This isn't the time
to be blaming each other!

568
00:38:53,080 --> 00:38:54,123
Get out.

569
00:38:54,206 --> 00:38:57,126
If you don't leave, I'm calling the cops.

570
00:38:57,209 --> 00:38:59,128
So get out! Leave!

571
00:39:00,129 --> 00:39:01,130
Let's go talk outside.

572
00:39:01,213 --> 00:39:02,173
Leave!

573
00:39:02,256 --> 00:39:04,550
- Get out. Out already!
- Come on!

574
00:39:04,633 --> 00:39:08,137
Choi Woo-su took responsibility
with his life. What about you?

575
00:39:08,637 --> 00:39:10,139
Are you all right?

576
00:39:11,015 --> 00:39:12,600
You asshole!

577
00:39:14,435 --> 00:39:15,686
You're a criminal.

578
00:39:16,896 --> 00:39:18,606
- Oh, gosh.
- Hurry up and leave!

579
00:39:18,689 --> 00:39:20,316
- Can you get up?
- Jong-il!

580
00:39:21,692 --> 00:39:24,278
Goodness. I don't think I can get up.

581
00:39:45,216 --> 00:39:50,429
NO CREAM SALES
CRIMINAL LEE HAE-SEOK OUT

582
00:40:09,323 --> 00:40:10,658
Be careful.

583
00:40:10,741 --> 00:40:11,784
My gosh.

584
00:40:11,867 --> 00:40:13,828
- I can't believe this!
- This is terrible.

585
00:40:15,955 --> 00:40:16,956
He must be hurt badly.

586
00:40:21,502 --> 00:40:24,338
Are you all right? Let's head inside.

587
00:40:25,506 --> 00:40:26,841
I'm sorry, ma'am.

588
00:40:27,550 --> 00:40:30,177
I'll clean up here.

589
00:40:35,433 --> 00:40:39,520
You must have a lot on your mind.
Just go inside, will you?

590
00:40:39,603 --> 00:40:43,983
Leave him be. He said he'll clean up.

591
00:40:45,234 --> 00:40:49,405
I'll take down the banner
at the community center.

592
00:40:49,488 --> 00:40:52,741
- Don't worry about that.
- You could get hurt too.

593
00:40:52,825 --> 00:40:56,579
Every house has been spray-painted.
Let's just go clean those.

594
00:40:56,662 --> 00:40:57,705
It's fine.

595
00:40:57,788 --> 00:41:02,168
This used to be a peaceful neighborhood!
How can this happen overnight?

596
00:41:02,251 --> 00:41:04,086
That's enough!

597
00:41:06,797 --> 00:41:08,132
I'm sorry.

598
00:41:09,967 --> 00:41:11,677
I'll sort things out as fast as I can

599
00:41:13,179 --> 00:41:15,139
and leave the village

600
00:41:15,806 --> 00:41:17,099
before I cause any more trouble.

601
00:41:27,735 --> 00:41:29,320
Why aren't you saying anything?

602
00:41:30,029 --> 00:41:32,573
How could you do this to him?

603
00:41:33,157 --> 00:41:35,034
How can you say that to us?

604
00:41:35,117 --> 00:41:37,953
You heard what they all said.

605
00:41:38,037 --> 00:41:41,415
Can you still take Mechoori's side
after hearing all that?

606
00:41:41,499 --> 00:41:42,708
Has…

607
00:41:43,834 --> 00:41:47,379
Has anyone here not received
Mechoori's help before?

608
00:41:47,463 --> 00:41:50,049
How can you be so ungrateful?

609
00:41:50,132 --> 00:41:51,759
You're the one who's being cold.

610
00:41:52,635 --> 00:41:57,139
We've been neighbors for over 30 years,
and you're putting him before us?

611
00:41:57,223 --> 00:42:01,268
Who is he to you?

612
00:42:01,352 --> 00:42:02,728
That's not what I meant.

613
00:42:02,811 --> 00:42:04,647
That's not it.

614
00:42:04,730 --> 00:42:08,108
For the first time,
let me ask you a favor.

615
00:42:10,486 --> 00:42:13,781
He's like my son.

616
00:42:13,864 --> 00:42:17,326
He's like the child I buried in my heart.

617
00:42:18,827 --> 00:42:23,123
The child I buried in my heart.

618
00:42:23,832 --> 00:42:26,794
He's like my own child.

619
00:42:27,670 --> 00:42:30,422
He's like my son.

620
00:42:42,518 --> 00:42:43,686
Bong-chan…

621
00:42:44,603 --> 00:42:46,897
Come home by dinnertime.
You'll ruin your health.

622
00:42:46,981 --> 00:42:48,941
I had a son.

623
00:42:49,650 --> 00:42:52,403
I did nothing for him,

624
00:42:52,486 --> 00:42:56,407
but he was a kind son
who always worried about me.

625
00:42:56,490 --> 00:43:00,160
What do we do?

626
00:43:00,244 --> 00:43:04,790
The boat Bong-chan was on went over.

627
00:43:06,417 --> 00:43:10,546
That day was my son's birthday.

628
00:43:13,591 --> 00:43:16,760
I couldn't even cook
warm soup for him on his birthdays.

629
00:43:18,012 --> 00:43:22,850
I should have made him some…

630
00:43:24,351 --> 00:43:25,352
Bong-chan…

631
00:43:27,521 --> 00:43:30,733
While living with regret,

632
00:43:30,816 --> 00:43:34,069
I saw Mechoori one day

633
00:43:35,237 --> 00:43:37,990
as I was on my way to visit Bong-chan.

634
00:43:46,999 --> 00:43:49,960
Excuse me. Hey.

635
00:43:51,795 --> 00:43:52,838
Young man.

636
00:43:52,921 --> 00:43:55,174
It's cold out here.

637
00:43:55,924 --> 00:43:59,261
Come on, let's go inside. It's cold.

638
00:44:03,015 --> 00:44:04,975
Mechoori.

639
00:44:06,226 --> 00:44:07,936
Have some potatoes.

640
00:44:08,020 --> 00:44:11,398
After feeding him
and spending time with him,

641
00:44:12,816 --> 00:44:18,238
I could see how foolishly kind he was,
just like my son.

642
00:44:20,824 --> 00:44:23,243
But that foolishness

643
00:44:24,036 --> 00:44:28,040
blew a warm spring breeze through my heart

644
00:44:29,166 --> 00:44:31,585
and our entire village.

645
00:44:37,007 --> 00:44:39,051
The heavens are so cruel.

646
00:44:40,386 --> 00:44:43,764
I wondered why they left me
all alone without my son,

647
00:44:45,933 --> 00:44:48,268
but I guess I was left here

648
00:44:49,770 --> 00:44:51,397
to hold your hand.

649
00:45:21,885 --> 00:45:23,637
Great work today.

650
00:45:32,020 --> 00:45:34,231
- What happened?
- Oh, gosh!

651
00:45:34,314 --> 00:45:35,858
So what did you do?

652
00:45:35,941 --> 00:45:36,984
So then, you know…

653
00:45:37,067 --> 00:45:39,361
It looked like a cow had licked it.

654
00:45:39,445 --> 00:45:41,780
- I really can't work with them.
- Me either.

655
00:45:41,864 --> 00:45:43,574
Ms. Ji Yun-ji.

656
00:45:45,659 --> 00:45:46,910
Congratulations on selling out.

657
00:45:47,870 --> 00:45:49,204
Can I talk to you for a minute?

658
00:45:50,289 --> 00:45:51,415
Let's go.

659
00:46:07,306 --> 00:46:09,141
You shouldn't come here.

660
00:46:09,683 --> 00:46:11,810
I wanted to treat you to something nice.

661
00:46:13,770 --> 00:46:15,647
The pre-release tester list
for Noori Cream

662
00:46:16,440 --> 00:46:18,400
was a great help.

663
00:46:20,235 --> 00:46:21,695
I'm done then, right?

664
00:46:22,613 --> 00:46:24,823
Don't ever visit me or contact me again.

665
00:46:26,033 --> 00:46:27,409
You really think…

666
00:46:29,119 --> 00:46:30,787
you can get off

667
00:46:31,413 --> 00:46:33,790
that easy, Ms. Ji?

668
00:46:33,874 --> 00:46:36,293
Mr. Son!

669
00:46:36,376 --> 00:46:40,255
The public reaction is getting pretty bad.
This should be enough.

670
00:46:40,339 --> 00:46:42,716
Who would buy the Noori Cream?

671
00:46:42,799 --> 00:46:46,929
Noori Cream was never my target, Ms. Ji.

672
00:46:47,012 --> 00:46:49,389
It was someone who still
hasn't learned his lesson

673
00:46:49,473 --> 00:46:51,225
after what happened five years ago.

674
00:46:52,976 --> 00:46:54,186
Lee Hae-seok.

675
00:46:55,395 --> 00:46:57,189
I have to finish him this time.

676
00:47:01,985 --> 00:47:03,862
What's the urgent news?

677
00:47:03,946 --> 00:47:07,574
I found out who Ms. Michelle
was meeting in secret.

678
00:47:11,995 --> 00:47:13,956
Who is this guy?

679
00:47:20,963 --> 00:47:22,923
Why would Chang-ho…

680
00:47:23,006 --> 00:47:25,842
Do you have any ideas as to why my sister

681
00:47:25,926 --> 00:47:27,386
would be meeting Son Chang-ho?

682
00:47:30,722 --> 00:47:32,140
One thing for sure

683
00:47:32,224 --> 00:47:35,811
is that there is no clear reason
why H.O. Cosmetics is buying

684
00:47:35,894 --> 00:47:37,771
Gojeuneok Bio's raw material.

685
00:47:37,854 --> 00:47:41,191
L'Étoile is currently planning
to enter the Asian market.

686
00:47:41,733 --> 00:47:42,734
But La Fin Essence

687
00:47:43,485 --> 00:47:45,612
was listed as a main product.

688
00:47:46,989 --> 00:47:48,532
La Fin Essence?

689
00:47:48,615 --> 00:47:50,492
Yes. Isn't that strange?

690
00:47:51,285 --> 00:47:54,621
They already used up
Gojeuneok Bio's materials a long time ago.

691
00:48:13,515 --> 00:48:16,184
UNITED IN PASSION,
NUAMER'S VISION COMES TO LIFE

692
00:48:18,979 --> 00:48:21,523
H.O. COSMETICS CLIENT LIST

693
00:48:27,988 --> 00:48:29,448
Who are you?

694
00:48:31,074 --> 00:48:32,075
Leave.

695
00:48:32,159 --> 00:48:33,660
We closed a long time ago.

696
00:48:34,870 --> 00:48:36,246
Do you know

697
00:48:36,955 --> 00:48:38,957
Son Chang-ho, by any chance?

698
00:48:41,376 --> 00:48:42,377
Who?

699
00:48:42,961 --> 00:48:45,631
I heard H.O. Cosmetics
and Nuamer signed an MoU

700
00:48:45,714 --> 00:48:48,300
and were co-developing products
until last year.

701
00:48:48,383 --> 00:48:52,220
All that talk about research,
collaboration, boosting technology…

702
00:48:53,138 --> 00:48:54,723
He was quite the smooth talker.

703
00:48:54,806 --> 00:48:58,268
We fell for it and signed the deal,

704
00:48:58,352 --> 00:49:00,687
and had all our core technology stolen.

705
00:49:00,771 --> 00:49:02,856
What about patents?
Did you not register any?

706
00:49:02,939 --> 00:49:08,528
How can small businesses like us
handle all those procedures and costs?

707
00:49:09,071 --> 00:49:12,574
Still, you must have your R&amp;D data
to be able to prove it.

708
00:49:12,658 --> 00:49:15,619
We tried every lawsuit we could think of,

709
00:49:15,702 --> 00:49:17,829
but we got hit with a countersuit
and lost everything.

710
00:49:17,913 --> 00:49:20,832
They'd already prepared
their own R&amp;D data.

711
00:49:21,416 --> 00:49:24,127
But I heard H.O. Cosmetics
has their own R&amp;D center

712
00:49:24,211 --> 00:49:26,046
and invests quite aggressively as well.

713
00:49:26,129 --> 00:49:27,506
Says who?

714
00:49:28,090 --> 00:49:31,218
They have no intention
of spending money on their products.

715
00:49:31,301 --> 00:49:34,680
They copied our new product
and switched the materials to cheap ones,

716
00:49:34,763 --> 00:49:37,474
then sold them at an even higher price.

717
00:49:37,557 --> 00:49:39,059
Hang on.

718
00:49:39,142 --> 00:49:40,811
What did you just say?

719
00:49:41,728 --> 00:49:43,105
They switched the materials?

720
00:49:43,188 --> 00:49:44,606
Yes.

721
00:49:44,690 --> 00:49:46,900
He said there was no need
for expensive materials

722
00:49:46,983 --> 00:49:49,861
and wanted to switch to cheaper ones
to improve margins.

723
00:49:50,612 --> 00:49:53,448
A businessman
should always prioritize margins.

724
00:49:53,532 --> 00:49:56,576
Woo-su switched the raw materials.

725
00:50:06,586 --> 00:50:09,297
You must have gotten mixed up
in Son Chang-ho's scheme as well.

726
00:50:09,798 --> 00:50:11,049
Be careful.

727
00:50:11,133 --> 00:50:12,592
If things don't go his way,

728
00:50:12,676 --> 00:50:14,928
he'll resort to anything, even violence.

729
00:50:24,312 --> 00:50:25,480
Ms. Moon.

730
00:50:26,940 --> 00:50:27,774
You're closed.

731
00:50:29,067 --> 00:50:31,820
Yes. I already turned off
all the machines.

732
00:50:31,903 --> 00:50:33,155
I see…

733
00:50:33,905 --> 00:50:36,283
I wanted a cup of your cappuccino.

734
00:50:37,743 --> 00:50:38,910
Too bad.

735
00:50:39,995 --> 00:50:41,705
I'll come back next time, then.

736
00:50:44,499 --> 00:50:45,500
Wait…

737
00:50:46,668 --> 00:50:50,505
I do have some alcohol, though.

738
00:51:00,849 --> 00:51:01,683
This is good.

739
00:51:05,896 --> 00:51:07,689
Is something going on?

740
00:51:07,773 --> 00:51:10,650
You're not acting cheesy today.

741
00:51:14,321 --> 00:51:15,947
Ms. Moon.

742
00:51:16,615 --> 00:51:20,243
Have you ever seen a hidden side
to someone close to you?

743
00:51:22,078 --> 00:51:25,957
I'm not even sure
who I've been spending time with,

744
00:51:27,751 --> 00:51:31,338
or whether I just never knew
who they really were.

745
00:51:31,922 --> 00:51:33,215
It's complicated.

746
00:51:34,841 --> 00:51:36,051
It's not complicated.

747
00:51:37,511 --> 00:51:39,095
The one who deceived you is bad,

748
00:51:40,180 --> 00:51:41,306
and the one who got fooled

749
00:51:42,891 --> 00:51:44,309
is just a victim.

750
00:51:49,523 --> 00:51:51,441
Don't feel upset over a bad person.

751
00:51:52,984 --> 00:51:53,985
That jerk

752
00:51:55,779 --> 00:51:58,031
has no clue

753
00:51:59,241 --> 00:52:00,909
how much you're suffering anyway.

754
00:52:02,869 --> 00:52:04,037
That jerk is the guy

755
00:52:05,372 --> 00:52:07,415
who wore the same watch as me, right?

756
00:52:13,588 --> 00:52:14,589
Yes.

757
00:52:37,904 --> 00:52:39,072
I…

758
00:52:40,031 --> 00:52:42,742
feel better if I have something warm
when I'm upset.

759
00:52:44,661 --> 00:52:45,745
Wait just a moment.

760
00:52:45,829 --> 00:52:48,290
I'll make you a warm cup of cappuccino.

761
00:53:10,854 --> 00:53:14,065
CANCEL THE LAUNCH BROADCAST
THIS IS GARBAGE

762
00:53:19,112 --> 00:53:21,031
MECHOORI

763
00:53:24,117 --> 00:53:26,453
HIT HWANG KI-HONG MD

764
00:53:27,537 --> 00:53:28,663
Mr. Hwang.

765
00:53:30,248 --> 00:53:31,249
Ms. Dam.

766
00:53:31,917 --> 00:53:34,044
The influencer Sensitive Assi…
Her name's Chu Min-a,

767
00:53:34,127 --> 00:53:36,630
and she was a pre-release tester.

768
00:53:36,713 --> 00:53:39,382
And all six people who made
the claims were testers too.

769
00:53:39,466 --> 00:53:41,092
Doesn't this seem strange?

770
00:53:41,176 --> 00:53:43,720
We distributed tons of samples
at our pop-up,

771
00:53:43,803 --> 00:53:46,681
but none of them had any issues with it.

772
00:53:46,765 --> 00:53:50,435
Then let's check the cream
that was given to the testers

773
00:53:50,518 --> 00:53:51,519
and run tests again.

774
00:53:53,480 --> 00:53:56,566
These are the results I just got.

775
00:53:58,944 --> 00:54:00,779
TEST RESULTS
PASS

776
00:54:00,862 --> 00:54:02,906
There's nothing wrong with the cream.

777
00:54:08,411 --> 00:54:09,829
Darn it.

778
00:54:11,790 --> 00:54:14,834
How can't a single one of them pick up?

779
00:54:14,918 --> 00:54:16,378
Are they all in this together?

780
00:54:16,461 --> 00:54:18,046
It seems like reverse viral marketing.

781
00:54:18,129 --> 00:54:20,799
We have to hurry and announce
that there aren't any issues.

782
00:54:21,466 --> 00:54:22,968
I know,

783
00:54:23,051 --> 00:54:26,513
but would anyone believe us
if we just say there's nothing wrong?

784
00:54:35,146 --> 00:54:36,398
Hello?

785
00:54:36,481 --> 00:54:38,149
It's me, Jin-yi.

786
00:54:40,694 --> 00:54:41,695
Jin-yi?

787
00:54:41,778 --> 00:54:43,613
Come on.

788
00:54:44,406 --> 00:54:46,241
I want to help Mechoori.

789
00:54:49,035 --> 00:54:52,914
My sister's skin
is practically litmus paper.

790
00:54:52,998 --> 00:54:54,749
She has chronic atopic dermatitis,

791
00:54:54,833 --> 00:54:56,835
so her skin reacts immediately

792
00:54:56,918 --> 00:54:58,420
to the slightest irritation.

793
00:54:59,004 --> 00:55:01,756
She's been using
this Noori Cream sample every day,

794
00:55:01,840 --> 00:55:04,050
but she hasn't shown any signs
of irritation.

795
00:55:04,134 --> 00:55:05,677
I FEEL RELIEVED SEEING THIS

796
00:55:05,760 --> 00:55:08,179
It doesn't feel itchy at all.

797
00:55:11,641 --> 00:55:15,311
This is the safety test report
we received from a testing lab

798
00:55:15,395 --> 00:55:17,564
designated by Korea's Ministry
of Food and Drug Safety.

799
00:55:17,647 --> 00:55:22,027
If you see the report here,
everything came back as "not detected."

800
00:55:22,610 --> 00:55:26,031
There wasn't a single substance
that was harmful.

801
00:55:34,706 --> 00:55:36,332
The thing you asked me to look into…

802
00:55:37,083 --> 00:55:39,461
The person who met with Ji Yun-ji…

803
00:55:39,544 --> 00:55:44,799
It was Son Chang-ho, the CEO
of H.O. Cosmetics, based in Thailand.

804
00:55:48,219 --> 00:55:49,721
THE USU, LEAD RESEARCHER

805
00:55:49,804 --> 00:55:51,598
There's one more thing.

806
00:55:53,725 --> 00:55:55,769
YUHAM CHILDREN'S PARK

807
00:55:55,852 --> 00:55:56,811
Seo-a!

808
00:55:57,771 --> 00:55:58,605
Climb up.

809
00:56:00,106 --> 00:56:01,775
Go on.

810
00:56:03,610 --> 00:56:06,029
To the side. Over there.

811
00:56:09,657 --> 00:56:10,825
Ms. Song.

812
00:56:11,701 --> 00:56:13,828
Oh, gosh. Ms. Song.

813
00:56:14,412 --> 00:56:15,455
How did you…

814
00:56:16,289 --> 00:56:20,418
I believe we have
a lot to talk about, Ms. Ji.

815
00:56:22,420 --> 00:56:25,298
Did you need something from me?

816
00:56:25,381 --> 00:56:27,884
How do you know Son Chang-ho?

817
00:56:29,511 --> 00:56:31,888
I heard you were supposed to do

818
00:56:32,680 --> 00:56:34,432
the Good Morning Cream broadcast.

819
00:56:35,725 --> 00:56:39,145
- Mom.
- Hey, Seo-a.

820
00:56:41,856 --> 00:56:46,194
I need to ask you
for a rather difficult favor.

821
00:56:46,778 --> 00:56:49,280
I have to protect my daughter too.

822
00:56:49,364 --> 00:56:51,116
Thank you so much, Jin-yi.

823
00:56:51,199 --> 00:56:54,744
It's nothing. I was able to muster up
my courage thanks to Som-yi.

824
00:56:54,828 --> 00:56:59,165
We should've mentioned that Mechoori
donates to the victims' group every month.

825
00:57:00,583 --> 00:57:03,086
I'm sure Mechoori
will be very grateful too.

826
00:57:03,169 --> 00:57:04,170
Ye-jin…

827
00:57:06,214 --> 00:57:09,342
Can I talk to you for a moment?

828
00:57:15,181 --> 00:57:16,766
Hae-seok.

829
00:57:17,934 --> 00:57:19,853
It's been such a long time.

830
00:57:19,936 --> 00:57:21,438
Yes, it's been a while.

831
00:57:21,521 --> 00:57:22,772
How have you been?

832
00:57:24,441 --> 00:57:26,151
I came to visit Woo-su.

833
00:57:57,640 --> 00:58:00,310
ARTICLE 3. UNIT PRICE AND ORDERS
418,000 WON PER KG

834
00:58:02,187 --> 00:58:04,355
ARTICLE 3. UNIT PRICE AND ORDERS
27,000 WON PER KG

835
00:58:24,584 --> 00:58:26,002
The home shopping host

836
00:58:27,712 --> 00:58:29,422
mentioned in gossip articles
five years ago

837
00:58:31,549 --> 00:58:33,259
about receiving a bribe…

838
00:58:37,430 --> 00:58:38,723
That was me.

839
00:58:41,059 --> 00:58:42,435
Are you a reporter?

840
00:58:42,519 --> 00:58:44,395
Are you trying to blackmail me with this?

841
00:58:45,188 --> 00:58:46,272
I'm not even a celebrity.

842
00:58:46,356 --> 00:58:48,441
What's so wrong with me
secretly having a child?

843
00:58:49,025 --> 00:58:49,901
Tell me!

844
00:58:50,693 --> 00:58:53,655
Calm down. I'm only here
to suggest we help each other.

845
00:58:54,322 --> 00:58:55,532
LISTING PROPOSAL

846
00:58:55,615 --> 00:58:57,200
I'm sure

847
00:58:57,283 --> 00:59:01,371
that you can easily get an item
on the list without an evaluation.

848
00:59:01,955 --> 00:59:05,625
If you list Good Morning Cream
on HIT's prime time slot,

849
00:59:06,584 --> 00:59:09,087
I'll give you money
with no strings attached.

850
00:59:11,381 --> 00:59:14,717
Just follow the proper procedures.

851
00:59:15,510 --> 00:59:16,928
Seo-a…

852
00:59:17,512 --> 00:59:20,348
needs her surgery, doesn't she?

853
00:59:25,812 --> 00:59:28,815
Chang-ho,
I'm asking you for the last time.

854
00:59:29,315 --> 00:59:31,234
Please reveal the truth.

855
00:59:32,360 --> 00:59:33,861
I won't leave you all alone.

856
00:59:33,945 --> 00:59:35,613
I'll take responsibility with you.

857
00:59:36,322 --> 00:59:38,616
I feel like I'm the one
who made you like this.

858
00:59:39,409 --> 00:59:40,535
I'm sorry.

859
00:59:42,120 --> 00:59:43,413
I'm sorry, Ye-jin.

860
00:59:44,163 --> 00:59:46,916
I shouldn't have done that to you

861
00:59:48,084 --> 00:59:50,837
just for my own sake.

862
00:59:55,592 --> 00:59:56,843
I know it's late,

863
00:59:58,469 --> 01:00:00,305
but I have something to give you.

864
01:00:10,231 --> 01:00:11,065
VOICE RECORDING

865
01:00:11,149 --> 01:00:12,275
It's all in there.

866
01:00:14,444 --> 01:00:16,321
It contains everything

867
01:00:17,697 --> 01:00:20,116
about how the Good Morning Cream
incident happened.

868
01:00:26,831 --> 01:00:28,374
CEO SON CHANG-HO

869
01:00:40,219 --> 01:00:42,513
Hae-seok, what brings you here?

870
01:00:49,812 --> 01:00:51,230
Explain this.

871
01:00:52,231 --> 01:00:54,233
What are you talking about?

872
01:00:57,320 --> 01:00:58,196
What is this?

873
01:00:58,279 --> 01:01:01,199
Don't ask. Just explain.

874
01:01:05,703 --> 01:01:07,830
You're the one who should explain.

875
01:01:08,498 --> 01:01:09,540
What's this about?

876
01:01:10,667 --> 01:01:12,085
Did you do this to Woo-su too?

877
01:01:16,589 --> 01:01:17,423
Hae-seok.

878
01:01:18,591 --> 01:01:21,052
You seem to be mistaken about something.

879
01:01:21,969 --> 01:01:23,888
Whatever it is,

880
01:01:23,971 --> 01:01:25,264
Woo-su will be upset

881
01:01:26,265 --> 01:01:29,143
seeing us having a conflict like this.

882
01:01:32,939 --> 01:01:36,734
Don't you dare say Woo-su's name
with that filthy mouth.

883
01:01:37,360 --> 01:01:39,320
Don't you get it, Hae-seok?

884
01:01:40,363 --> 01:01:42,115
You've been deceived by him too.

885
01:01:42,198 --> 01:01:44,242
That's the truth!

886
01:01:53,710 --> 01:01:55,294
Mr. Son!

887
01:01:55,378 --> 01:01:57,338
You said there was nothing wrong
with the product.

888
01:01:57,422 --> 01:01:58,631
Someone might see us.

889
01:01:58,715 --> 01:02:01,676
You said you used cheaper materials,
but there wouldn't be any issues.

890
01:02:03,553 --> 01:02:05,304
Are you questioning me right now?

891
01:02:06,347 --> 01:02:09,517
Ms. Ji, why are you suddenly
pretending to be naive?

892
01:02:10,309 --> 01:02:13,438
Did you really think there wouldn't be
any risks when you received the money?

893
01:02:14,147 --> 01:02:15,231
No,

894
01:02:15,314 --> 01:02:17,400
you handed the show
to your junior because you knew.

895
01:02:17,483 --> 01:02:18,317
Be honest.

896
01:02:19,235 --> 01:02:20,570
Did you really not know?

897
01:02:20,653 --> 01:02:22,196
Did you not?

898
01:02:26,033 --> 01:02:27,785
That's the truth.

899
01:02:30,830 --> 01:02:32,999
And that's why Woo-su died.

900
01:02:44,218 --> 01:02:45,219
Chang-ho.

901
01:02:46,262 --> 01:02:49,182
You said you'd take care of this

902
01:02:49,265 --> 01:02:51,309
when I was on a business trip
to Jeju Island, right?

903
01:02:52,393 --> 01:02:53,478
What are you talking about?

904
01:02:55,688 --> 01:02:57,398
When did I say that?

905
01:02:58,107 --> 01:03:01,486
Chang-ho, just be honest with me.

906
01:03:01,569 --> 01:03:03,446
Please. Just tell me.

907
01:03:05,406 --> 01:03:09,368
Woo-su, I know you're standing
on the edge of a cliff right now,

908
01:03:10,286 --> 01:03:11,662
but you shouldn't do this.

909
01:03:13,581 --> 01:03:16,042
You're the one who switched
the material, you jerk!

910
01:03:21,005 --> 01:03:22,507
Do you have proof?

911
01:03:25,384 --> 01:03:26,469
You…

912
01:03:27,261 --> 01:03:28,095
You didn't, right?

913
01:03:29,931 --> 01:03:31,182
Tell me it wasn't you!

914
01:03:31,766 --> 01:03:33,768
It wasn't, right? Tell me!

915
01:03:34,268 --> 01:03:35,436
It wasn't you, was it?

916
01:03:37,772 --> 01:03:38,981
How could you…

917
01:03:40,107 --> 01:03:42,193
Please tell me it wasn't you!

918
01:03:44,195 --> 01:03:46,697
It wasn't you, right? Chang-ho, please!

919
01:03:53,496 --> 01:03:55,748
SOLD OUT ON YOU

920
01:03:55,832 --> 01:04:01,754
THANKS TO SPECIAL GUEST SEO HYUN-WOO

921
01:05:00,813 --> 01:05:02,815
Subtitle translation by: Juyoung Park
